data.name: Spicy Baked Bean Tacos
data.quickTastyDescription: Easy and flavorful tacos filled with spicy baked beans, topped with fresh veggies and cheese.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a medium saucepan, heat the canned baked beans over medium heat. Stir in the chili powder, salt, and pepper to taste. Allow to simmer for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
While the beans are heating, brush both sides of the corn tortillas lightly with olive oil and place them on a baking sheet.
Bake the tortillas in the preheated oven for 5-7 minutes, until they are crispy but not burnt.
Remove the tortillas from the oven and spoon the spicy baked beans into each tortilla.
Top with shredded cheese, sour cream, salsa, and chopped fresh cilantro.
